All Contacts.vcf
My Contacts.vcf
Starred in Android.vcf

Data included

Contacts and contact photos you added yourself, as well as contacts saved from your interactions in Google products like Gmail.

Folder structure

Now that youve downloaded the contacts from your Google Account, youll find folders named My Contacts and All Contacts, plus additional folders if you created any labels, or starred contacts on your Android device. The My Contacts folder contains only those contacts you added yourself. The All Contacts folder contains both contacts you added yourself as well as contact info automatically saved from your interactions in Google products, like Gmail.

How to handle this export

If you downloaded your contacts as a CSV file, you can view them in a spreadsheet, or import them to Microsoft Outlook or another Google Account. If you downloaded your contacts as a vCard file, you can import them to another Google Account, Mac OS, iOS, or other contacts services.

Google Account

Manage your info, privacy, and make Google work better for you
Below are all the possible formats you could have received in your archive:
Home App data
Devices, rooms, homes and automations.
JSON
"Devices" and "Rooms" are contained in "RoomsAndDevices" objects, which are contained in "FullStructure" objects.Devices not in a structure are included as "unassigned_devices".
Home history data
History of events in your home.
JSON
Events in your home are listed under "structure_history." Events about a specific device are listed under "device_history". "Timestamp" is the time of the event.
Audio recordings
Audio recordings at the time sound sensing devices detected activity.
audio/aac
Audio recordings are found in the "blobs" folder and end with the ".aac" suffix.
Security alarm clip data
List of security alarm clip data which belong to your home.
JSON
All the clip data are under an array named "securityAlarmClipData" which is contained in another array named "securityAlarmData"
Professional services data
Information about professional services (e.g. installation services) you have ordered.
JSON
"partnerName" is the name of the partner offering the professional service. "installation.location" is the location where the installation service is taking place. "installation.deviceSettings" are the default settings you have selected for the devices set up during the installation.
Scripted Automations
Automations created in the Google Home Script Editor.
JSON
"script" is the name of the script containing automations created by script editor
Platform Permission Data
Permissions you have granted to third-party applications to access your smart-home data, including automations, devices, rooms, and structures.
JSON
Phone and permission grants for third party applications. "Timestamp" is the time you granted access to the application. Grants are the specific permissions you approved.

All mail Including Spam and Trash.mbox

Data included

Messages and attachments in your Gmail account in MBOX format. User settings from your Gmail account in JSON format.

Folder structure

For user settings, we provide a separate folder with each exported setting in their individual JSON file. For messages, we provide all of your mail in a single mbox file by default.Alternatively, you can choose labels to export, each of which will be contained in its own mbox file. When you export your mail from Gmail, each message's labels are preserved in a special X-Gmail-Labels header, in CSV format. While no mail client recognizes this header now, most mail clients allow for extensions to be written that could make use of this data.

Phones.vcf

Data included

Your saved Google Voice call history, messages and voicemails as well as current linked numbers.

Folder structure

The compressed file will include:
Calls folder: all calls made, received and missed.
Greetings folder: mp3s of recorded greetings.
VCF file including all phone numbers registered with Voice.
HTML file including all billed calls and costs.

How to handle this export

Common file decompression tools can be used to unpack the contents once the compressed file has been downloaded. Many file management systems like Google Drive will provide this functionality.

You're in control of your data in Voice

Manage your data

Archive or delete messages, calls, or voicemails

activity-feed.json

Data included

Your flows and activity log.

Folder structure

We provide all your flows in separate JSON files, each titled with the name of the flow. Your activity log for all flows is exported in a single JSON file, named activity-log.json.

subscriptions.csv

Data included

Watch and search history, videos, comments and other content you've created on YouTube and YouTube Music

Folder structure

Each type of your YouTube data is in its own subfolder.

How to handle this export

Each CSV file includes data about a specific YouTube object (or type of object). The columns are properties, and the rows are different instances.
